WEBVTT

00:00.801 --> 00:02.835
In new york city's
war on crime,

00:02.836 --> 00:05.104
The worst criminal offenders
are pursued

00:05.105 --> 00:07.840
By the detectives
of the major case squad.

00:07.841 --> 00:10.109
These are their stories.

00:18.986 --> 00:20.820
- Thank you for listening
to this whole thing.

00:20.821 --> 00:24.724
I hope I, uh--
I can put it behind me.

00:27.861 --> 00:33.466
As my friend,
I thought you'd understand.

00:33.467 --> 00:36.736
I guess in the end,
it was just about a book.

00:36.737 --> 00:39.939
- You know, I don't think
you came all the way to london

00:39.940 --> 00:41.474
To talk about a book.

00:41.475 --> 00:43.709
- What do you mean?

00:43.710 --> 00:46.646
- I mean...
It's about all the rest of it.

00:46.647 --> 00:49.982
It's about her.

00:49.983 --> 00:53.052
And you have to put it
behind you.

00:55.022 --> 00:58.257
- Well, you say that
like it's, uh, easy, you know?

00:58.258 --> 01:01.027
- No one said
life was easy.

01:01.028 --> 01:02.895
- It's like time stood still
or something.

01:02.896 --> 01:05.096
It was like something
out of dickens.

01:05.098 --> 01:07.233
- No, zachary,
it was out of your life.

01:07.234 --> 01:11.037
That was the problem.

01:11.038 --> 01:14.340
- I didn't think it would
get to me like that, you know?

01:14.341 --> 01:17.210
- And that was
your second problem.

01:20.514 --> 01:22.682
- You know,
if you'd told me that...

01:22.683 --> 01:25.985
I was gonna be there
in that house...

01:25.986 --> 01:28.788
On that day with her...

01:28.789 --> 01:33.526
Feeling the things
that I did...

01:33.527 --> 01:36.262
I wouldn't have
believed it.

01:40.667 --> 01:42.902
- What's up?

01:42.903 --> 01:46.005
- Uh, ask me
at the end of the day.

01:46.006 --> 01:47.573
- You okay?

01:47.574 --> 01:52.612
- Two dead inside.
Dylan weld, 36, art dealer.

01:52.613 --> 01:57.049
And palmer abrigaille, 72,
dealer,

01:57.050 --> 01:58.317
And collector
of rare books.

01:58.318 --> 02:01.587
It appears--

02:01.588 --> 02:05.057
It appears that they, uh...
Killed each other.

02:05.058 --> 02:08.261
Appears...

02:08.262 --> 02:09.395
Oh, boy.

02:09.395 --> 02:12.331
It's a little bit strange
for me.

02:12.332 --> 02:14.367
I know the abrigailles.

02:14.368 --> 02:17.770
- Zach, I'm sorry.

02:17.771 --> 02:19.739
You wanna take the day?

02:19.740 --> 02:23.543
- No, no.
I'll be okay.

02:23.544 --> 02:26.879
I told her I'd be okay.

02:26.880 --> 02:29.782
The truth was
I didn't know what I'd be.

02:29.783 --> 02:35.154
I mean, it was like
I was walking into my own past.

02:38.191 --> 02:40.560
- A swordfight.

02:40.561 --> 02:42.428
Some kind of duel?

02:42.429 --> 02:45.598
- Any violent confrontation

02:45.599 --> 02:48.467
Was very,
very unlike palmer.

02:48.468 --> 02:50.836
- Well, in any case,

02:50.837 --> 02:53.306
They died around 2:00 a.M.,

02:53.307 --> 02:56.275
And the cause appears to be
exsanguination for both.

02:56.276 --> 02:58.578
- The way his sword is held--

02:58.579 --> 03:00.379
It's in his right hand.

03:00.380 --> 03:03.950
Palmer had nerve damage
from a shooting accident.

03:03.951 --> 03:06.886
Poor control of his thumb.

03:06.887 --> 03:10.423
We need to do extensive
blood spatter work here, please.

03:10.424 --> 03:12.058
- I'll get them on it.
- Thank you.

03:12.059 --> 03:13.960
Where's his daughter?
- Uh...

03:13.961 --> 03:15.828
They got her back there.

03:15.829 --> 03:19.799
- I think it's best
if she sees a familiar face.

03:24.571 --> 03:26.772
Lenore?

03:28.909 --> 03:30.977
- Yes, come in.
Sorry.

03:30.978 --> 03:33.112
I'm a bit lost.

03:33.113 --> 03:36.215
There are so many people here.

03:42.122 --> 03:44.557
Zachary.

03:44.558 --> 03:45.925
- Hi.

03:45.926 --> 03:49.328
- Oh...
[sniffles]

03:52.165 --> 03:55.067
Do you know what...
Happened here?

03:55.068 --> 04:00.072
- Between dylan weld
and your father.

04:00.073 --> 04:01.841
I'm looking into that.

04:01.842 --> 04:04.377
- How is my father?

04:04.378 --> 04:06.278
I'm so worried.

04:06.279 --> 04:07.847
- Has nobody told you...

04:07.848 --> 04:09.749
Told you anything?

04:09.750 --> 04:11.751
- No, they...

04:11.752 --> 04:14.620
They brought me back here
and, uh...

04:14.621 --> 04:17.322
I--no.

04:17.324 --> 04:20.091
- I'm so sorry.

04:20.093 --> 04:23.329
Your father...

04:23.330 --> 04:26.532
Is gone.

04:26.533 --> 04:29.301
- What do you mean?
Do you mean--

04:29.302 --> 04:30.970
- He's been killed.

04:36.109 --> 04:38.911
So, so sorry.

